Hi I have 2 guineas who are only 3 months old - can anyone tell me how
often they need their claws trimming and also how old they might be
before they need trimming.  This is the first time we have had any pets
so are learning all the time.

Michelle
</POST>
<POST>
<POSTER> "ellenvega" &lt;ellenv...@gmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-01-11T15:39:00 </POSTDATE>
I trim my pigs' nails about once a month.  You'll probably want to
start clipping soon now, even if their nails really don't need it you
can just take off a little and get them used to it.  I use a regular
human fingernail clipper.  Read through:
http://www.guinealynx.info/nails.html

If you're a new owner, I strongly suggest you read through this
beginner's guide:
http://www.guinealynx.info/healthycavy.html
</POST>
<POST>
<POSTER> &lt;n...@thematrix.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-01-12T15:53:00 </POSTDATE>
If you are new to the game I would be tempted to visit the vet first and ask
them to show you the ropes. They are quite delicate (GPs) and if they are
scared they might jump and hurt themselves.

Best of luck when you do get into it though! Ours is a nightmare and manages
to pull his feet away just as you are about to close the clippers!

