I just assisted my wife in doing this to our piggie Ginger at lunchtime
today.   She was quite co-operative and can usually be fairly skittish.  I
was the one with a good grip on her, and reassuring words in her ear (they
do help if said in a low tone).  It's been about 2.5 months since her last
clipping and I found one claw had nails that were waaay too long.

We got our vet to show us how he did it, and he sold us some clippers I
think that are made for small animals such as GP's.  They cost nearly $10
but do the job quickly.

Make sure there is a lot of light so you can see where the quick is...we
won't attempt it in the evening because there's not enough light, we find.

Now, to examine my other two...

